.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH SM 1  "sm 0.1.0" 
.SH NAME
sm \- CLI for managing security projects and engagements
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBsm\fR [\fB\-w\fR|\fB\-\-workspace\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
CLI for managing security projects and engagements
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-w\fR, \fB\-\-workspace\fR \fI<WORKSPACE>\fR
Workspace by name (from global config) or path
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
sm\-new(1)
Create a new workspace, client, project, engagement, or template
.TP
sm\-ls(1)
List entities
.TP
sm\-show(1)
Show entity details
.TP
sm\-edit(1)
Open config in $EDITOR
.TP
sm\-rm(1)
Remove an entity (requires \-\-force)
.TP
sm\-status(1)
Show current workspace info
.TP
sm\-check(1)
Check workspace health
.TP
sm\-config(1)
Show or set global configuration
.TP
sm\-stats(1)
Show workspace or client statistics
.TP
sm\-finding(1)
Manage findings
.TP
sm\-req(1)
Manage requirements
.TP
sm\-scope(1)
Open scope.md in editor
.TP
sm\-note(1)
Create a quick note
.TP
sm\-report(1)
Build a report
.TP
sm\-sow(1)
Build a SOW
.TP
sm\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH VERSION
v0.1.0
